qas.question: What corridor is Oklahoma City situated in?
When was the Oklahoma City bombing?
What was the name of the building involved in the bombing?

context: Oklahoma City is on the <a0_0>I-35 Corridor<a0_0/> and is one of the primary travel corridors into neighboring Texas and Mexico. Located in the Frontier Country region of the state, the city's northeast section lies in an ecological region known as the Cross Timbers. The city was founded during the Land Run of <a1_0>1889<a1_0/>, and grew to a population of over 10,000 within hours of its founding. The city was the scene of the April 19, <a2_0>1995<a2_0/> bombing of the <a3_0>Alfred P. Murrah Federal Building<a3_0/>, in which 168 people died. It was the deadliest terror attack in the history of the United States until the attacks of September 11, 2001, and remains the deadliest act of domestic terrorism in U.S. history.
